POLICE Scotland should be ­applauded for listening to the public in its U-turn over armed police, the First Minister has said. Armed cops move hailed POLICE Scotland should be ­applauded for listening to the public in its U-turn over armed police, the First Minister has said.Alex Salmond defended the force's decision to restrict the deployment of armed officers to life-threatening incidents or those involving firearms following political and public concern about guns being carried on routine patrols.A review by chief constable Sir Stephen House concluded that the 275 officers attached to armed response vehicles will not be dispatched to routine incidents.Labour MSP Graeme Pearson said Justice Secretary Kenny MacAskill should have urged SPA members to &quot;take steps at a much earlier stage to allay justified public concerns&quot;. 